The Plateau State Police Command says it has arrested some suspected killers of AIG Christopher Dega (retd.), a Senior Special Assistant to Benue State Governor Samuel Ortom on Security. SaharaReporters had reported how the governor’s aide was killed in Jos, the Plateau state capital.  The Police Public Relations Officer in Plateau, Ubah Ogaba, confirmed the incident in a statement on Wednesday. The statement read, “The Plateau State Police Command on a sad note received an ugly report of the death of AIG Christopher Dega (Rtd).



